  "Description": "The AssertFailed goal is designed to handle assertion errors by outputting a failure message and the specific error message associated with the assertion failure. It first writes a generic failure message indicating that an assertion error has occurred, followed by a detailed error message that is provided as input. This goal is useful for debugging and logging purposes when assertions in the code do not hold true.",
